  "summary": "Can t fly in creative",
  "environment_raw": null,
  "description": "Every time I try to fly in creative all I do is jump, I checked settings and restarted the game and still can t fly in creative, even making a new world didn t work, sorry I don t have a picture to prove. n n",
  "Steps to Reproduce": "1. Launch Minecraft and select \"Singleplayer\" from the main menu.\n2. Create a new world and set the game mode to \"Creative\".\n3. Enter the world once it has loaded.\n4. Ensure you are on the ground and not in a vehicle or riding an entity.\n5. Double-tap the jump key (default is Space) to attempt to activate flying.\n6. Observe the behavior; instead of flying, the character only jumps.\n7. Check the game settings to confirm that \"Allow Flying\" is enabled.\n8. Restart the game and repeat steps 2-6 to see if the issue persists.\n9. Create a new world again with the same settings and repeat steps 4-6 to confirm the bug occurs in multiple worlds.",
  "Environment": "Minecraft Java Edition Versions: 1.21.8, 25w32a (includes snapshots)",
  "Observed Behavior": "When attempting to fly in Creative mode, the player is unable to initiate flight and instead only performs a jump. The expected behavior of flying, which is activated by double-tapping the jump key (default: Space), does not occur. Despite verifying that the game is set to Creative mode, restarting the game, and creating a new world, the issue persists. The player is unable to gain altitude or move while flying, and the controls for ascending (jump) and descending (sneak) do not function as intended. This issue occurs across all worlds tested, indicating a potential game-wide bug affecting the flying mechanics in Creative mode. No visual evidence is available to support the report, but the behavior is consistently reproducible under the described conditions.",
  "Expected Behavior": "When in Creative mode, the player should be able to initiate flight by double-tapping the jump key (default is Space). Once flying, the player can ascend by holding the jump key and descend by holding the sneak key (default is Shift). The player should be able to move freely in any direction while flying, and this ability should not be impeded by any game settings or world conditions. If the player touches the ground while flying, flying should automatically disable, but the player should be able to reactivate it by double-tapping the jump key again. If the player is unable to fly despite following these controls, it indicates a malfunction in the game's flying mechanics in Creative mode.",
